Which of the following commands, executed from within the UEFI shell, controls the bootconfiguration?
A)  bootcfg
B)  bcfg
C)  grub- install
D)  grcfg
B
B. The bcfg command within the UEFI shell is used to configure bootloaders on a UEFI-based system. The command can accept various parameters to configure how the boot-loader and kernel will load on boot. Of the other commands shown, grub- install isvalid but not within the UEFI shell.
